review:
Let's bring freedom to Afganistan, f u c k yeah!
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U1mlCPMYtPk
This game reminded me old on-rails shooters that l played a long time ago when I was a kid. And now because of the game I started to love on-rails shooters again. Thanx for refreshing my memory!

Pros:
+Fun for 1-2 hours;
+High quality for the rare genre "On-Rails Shooter";
+Voice acting (it's not horrible at least);
+Achievements, trading cards, steam cloud, steam leaderboards, remote play...
+-Plot of the game could be better, but it doesn't really matter, because we're here to shoot

Cons:
-We can't pick veteran difficulty in the begging;
-Too easy (In the sequel "Heavy Fire: Shattered Spear" will be harder enough) ;
-Bad lightning (u can't see somethimes ur enemies because of that);

Just don't mind "mixed" reviews. Try to enjoy the game. It's worth it. But buy it ONLY at a discount!
